    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Jim to Mon. Paul Rockwell <date value="1916-06-26">June 26th ‘15</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1915-06-26">June 26th ‘15</date></dateline>
        			
            <salute>
            Dear Paul:
            </salute></opener>
        		
        		<p>
            I finished a long letter
            to you to day which I have
            been delaying on account of our
            staff car which for some reason
            or another fails to show up.
            I kept putting off writing waiting
            for the auto to send the letter 
            back by.  No special news in
            it however.  Just a few
            minutes ago I received your
            welcome postal of the 22nd
            sent by Secteur Postal 84
            and saying that you had
            mailed a letter by old
            address.  It beat the convoi
            d’automobiles so use the 
            Secteur Postal 84 after this.
                        
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            I will hold my letter for
            the staff car, which certainly
            ought to be out by tomorrow 
            or the next day, and
            send this in by usual
            route.
            </p><p>
            Hope to get a lot of
            news from you in
            your letter for its
            been a long time since I’ve
            had news of you or
            your brother or fiancee.
            Hope things are 
            running along in
                        
            <pb n="[p.3]"/>
            
            good shape now.
            </p><p>
            By the way please let me
            know how long it takes
            for you to get this note,
            I want to figure how
            many days our mail is
            held up.  Some say four.
            </p><p>
            Things running well here
            and everyone well and
            happy.  We haven’t had
            a bombardment in so long
            long [sic] we’re getting lonesome
            for it.  I’ll slip you
            another note soon.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <signed>Jim</signed>
        		</closer>
        		
            
            <!-- [This letter and envelope are all of a piece. It is addressed to Mon. Paul Rockwell, Chez M. le Vicomte du Peloux, 15 Avenue Malakoff, Paris.] -->
            
            </div1>
        </body>
